    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*haϑya-</w><gloss><q>истинный</q></gloss></mentioned> (как <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_acc"/> ‘дикая утка’ из %iāti-%i, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_wærcc"/> ‘перепел’ из %ivartika-%i). На иранской почве, за пределами
        древнеиранских языков, слово представлено слабо; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>haṭhṭha</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из %ihaϑya-%i)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from
            %ihaϑya-%i)</note><gloss><q>правда</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>истина</q></gloss></mentioned>, (с геминацией %iṭhṭh%i, как в
        осетинском; ср., впрочем: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Konow._SSt."
            /><biblScope>8—9</biblScope></bibl>); на древнеарийской почве ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>haiϑya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>hašiya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>satyá-</w><gloss><q>истинный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>истина</q></gloss></mentioned>, (один из важнейших моральных
        терминов древних индийцев). С наращением излюбленного суффикса %i-æg%i слово дано в виде
        общераспространенного <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æcæg"/> ‘истинный’. Эту же основу
        усматриваем в %iæv-acc-æg-æn%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæccægæn"/>] ‘вероятно’,
        æv-æʒ-i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæʒi"/>] id., æv-æʒ-a [<ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ævæʒa"/>] ‘по правде говоря’; см. эти слова, а также <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æcægælon"/> ‘чужой’.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*haϑya-</w><gloss><q>true</q></gloss></mentioned> (like <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_acc"/> ‘wild duck’ from %iāti-%i, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_wærcc"/> ‘quail’ из %ivartika-%i). On Iranian ground, outside of the
        ancient Iranian languages, the word is poorly represented; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>haṭhṭha</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из %ihaϑya-%i)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from
            %ihaϑya-%i)</note><gloss><q>true</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>truth</q></gloss></mentioned>, (with gemination %iṭhṭh%i like on
        Ossetic; however, consider <bibl><ref target="#ref_Konow._SSt."
            /><biblScope>8—9</biblScope></bibl>); on ancient Aryan ground cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>haiϑya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>hašiya-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>satyá-</w><gloss><q>true</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>truth</q></gloss></mentioned>, (one of the most important
        moral terms of the ancient Indians). With the augment of the favorite suffix %i-æg%i, the
        word is given in the form of the common<ref type="xr" target="#entry_æcæg"/> ‘true’. The
        same stem is attested in %iæv-acc-æg-æn%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæccægæn"/>]
        ‘probably’, %iæv-æʒ-i%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævæʒi"/>] id., %iæv-æʒ-a%i [<ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_ævæʒa"/>] ‘to tell the truth’; see these items and <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_æcægælon"/> ‘alien’.</etym>
</entry>
